relationships.tail: typePath must be an instance of TypePath or null

relationships.head: org.springframework.asm.TypePath#put(TypePath,ByteVector)
relationships.tail: static void put(final TypePath typePath, final ByteVector output) { if (typePath == null) { output.putByte(0); } else { int length = typePath.typePathContainer[typePath.typePathOffset] * 2 + 1; output.putByteArray(typePath.typePathContainer, typePath.typePathOffset, length); } }

relationships.head: org.springframework.asm.TypePath#put(TypePath,ByteVector)
relationships.tail: This method is used to serialize the type path into a ByteVector. It handles null values by putting a single byte (0) into the output. For non-null TypePath instances, it calculates the length of the type path and puts the corresponding bytes into the output.

relationships.head: org.springframework.asm.TypePath#put(TypePath,ByteVector)
relationships.tail: The design principle behind this method is to provide a straightforward and efficient way to serialize type paths. It ensures that the output format adheres to the JVMS structure, making it suitable for use in environments that require strict compliance with the Java Virtual Machine Specification.
